# Document Rules

## Documentation Standards
- Use Markdown (.md) format for all documentation
- Follow consistent formatting and structure
- Include table of contents for long documents
- Use clear, descriptive headings

## File Organization
- Use descriptive filenames with dates when applicable
- Organize documents by category and priority
- Maintain version control for important documents
- Archive outdated documents appropriately

## Content Guidelines
- Write clear, concise, and actionable content
- Use bullet points and numbered lists for clarity
- Include code examples where relevant
- Add diagrams for complex processes

## Review Process
- Peer review for important documents
- Regular updates and maintenance
- Version control and change tracking
- Approval workflow for critical documents

## Templates
- Use consistent templates for different document types
- Include standard sections (overview, requirements, etc.)
- Maintain branding and formatting consistency
- Provide examples and best practices